=== Pixel and Pixel XL ===
{{main|Pixel (1st generation)}}
[[File:Pixel 1 and 1 XL front.svg|thumb|Pixel and Pixel XL smartphones]]
[[File:Google Pixel and Pixel XL smartphones (30155272575).jpg|thumb|"Very Silver" and "Quite Black" Pixel smartphones]]

Google announced the first generation Pixel smartphones, the '''Pixel,''' and the '''Pixel XL''', on October 4, 2016, during the #MadeByGoogle event.<ref name="verge-pixelannounce">{{cite web |title=Pixel 'Phone by Google' Announced |url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/10/4/13161028/google-phone-announced-pixel-xl-price-release-date-specs |website=The Verge |date=October 4, 2016|access-date=October 4, 2016}}</ref> Google emphasized the camera on the two phones, which ranked as the best smartphone camera on DxOMarkMobile with 90{{nbsp}}points until [[HTC]] released the [[HTC U11|U11]], which also scored 90{{nbsp}}points.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dxomark.com/Mobiles|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018184136/http://www.dxomark.com/Mobiles|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 18, 2013 |title=DxOMark Mobile |website=Dxomark.com |language=en|access-date=February 21, 2017}}</ref> This is largely due to software optimizations such as HDR+. The Pixel phones also include unlimited cloud storage for pictures on [[Google Photos]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/10/4/13163338/google-is-giving-free-unlimited-original-quality-photo-and-video |title=Google is giving free, unlimited original-quality photo and video backups with the Pixel phones |date=October 4, 2016 |website=The Verge|access-date=March 21, 2017}}</ref> and, for devices purchased directly from Google, an [[Bootloader unlocking|unlockable bootloader]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://android.gadgethacks.com/news/its-official-pixel-phones-from-google-store-will-be-rootable-with-unlockable-bootloaders-0174285/ |title=It's Official: Pixel Phones from the Google Store Will Be Rootable with Unlockable Bootloaders |work=WonderHowTo|access-date=October 6, 2017 |language=en}}</ref> In 2019, a class action lawsuit<ref>{{Cite web |last=Villas-Boas |first=Antonio |title=Google Pixel owners have a week to get up to $500 as the result of a lawsuit over faulty microphones — here's how to claim your money |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/google-pixel-microphone-lawsuit-how-file-claim-for-settlement-money-2019-8|access-date=February 12, 2021 |website=[[Business Insider]]}}</ref> over faulty microphones in some devices enabled Pixel owners to claim up to $500 in compensation.

* Display: 5.0" 60{{nbsp}}[[Refresh rate|Hz]] AMOLED display with 1080×1920 pixel resolution (Pixel); 5.5" AMOLED 60&nbsp;Hz display with 1440×2560 pixel resolution (Pixel XL)
* Processor: Qualcomm [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems on chips#Snapdragon 800 series (2013–2021)|Snapdragon 821]]
* Storage: UFS 2.0 with 32&nbsp;GB or 128&nbsp;GB
* [[Random-access memory|RAM]]: 4&nbsp;GB [[LPDDR#LPDDR4|LPDDR4]]
* Cameras: 12.3{{nbsp}}[[Pixel#Megapixel|MP]] rear camera Sony Exmor IMX378<ref>{{Citation |title=Choosing a Lens |date=January 25, 2013 |url=http://dx.doi.org/10.4324/9780080888248-15 |work=Sony Software |pages=87–95 |publisher=Routledge |doi=10.4324/9780080888248-15 |isbn=978-0-08-088824-8|access-date=March 9, 2022|url-access=subscription}}</ref> sensor with f/2.0 lens and IR laser-assisted autofocus;<ref name="IMX378-XDA" /> 1.55 μm pixel size.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |url=https://madeby.google.com/intl/de_de/phone/ |title=Google Pixel product page |website=Made by Google |language=de|access-date=February 21, 2017}}</ref> 8 MP front camera with f/2.4 lens
* Headphone Jack
* Battery: 2,770{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel); 3,450{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel XL); both are non-removable and have fast charging
* Materials: Aluminum unibody design with hybrid coating; IP53 water and dust resistance
* Colors: Very Silver {{Colorbox|#c5c5c3}}, Quite Black {{Colorbox|Black}} or Really Blue {{Colorbox|#6483f8}} (Limited Edition)
* Operating system: [[Android Nougat|Android 7.1 Nougat]]; upgradable to [[Android 10]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://android-developers.googleblog.com/2019/03/introducing-android-q-beta.html |title=Introducing Android Q Beta |date=March 13, 2019 |website=Android Developers Blog|access-date=March 14, 2019}}</ref>

=== Pixel 2 and 2 XL ===
{{main|Pixel 2}}
[[File:Pixel 2 and 2 XL front.svg|thumb|Pixel 2 and Pixel 2 XL smartphones]]
Google announced the Pixel 2 series, consisting of the '''Pixel 2''' and '''Pixel 2 XL''', on October 4, 2017.

* Display: 5.0" AMOLED 60&nbsp;Hz display with 1080×1920 pixel resolution (Pixel 2); 6" P-OLED 60&nbsp;Hz display with 1440×2880 pixel resolution (Pixel 2 XL); Both displays have Corning Gorilla Glass 5
* Processor: Qualcomm [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems on chips#Snapdragon 800 series (2013–2021)|Snapdragon 835]]
* Storage: UFS 2.1 with 64&nbsp;GB or 128&nbsp;GB
* RAM: 4&nbsp;GB [[LPDDR#LPDDR4X|LPDDR4X]]
* Cameras: 12.2{{nbsp}}[[Pixel#Megapixel|MP]] rear camera Sony Exmor IMX362 with f/1.8 lens, IR laser-assisted autofocus, optical and electronic [[image stabilization]]; 8 MP front camera with f/2.4 lens
* Battery: 2,700{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel 2); 3,520{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel 2 XL); both are non-removable and have fast charging
* Materials: Aluminum unibody design with hybrid coating; IP67 water and dust resistance
* Colors: Just Black {{Colorbox|Black}}, Clearly White {{Colorbox|White}} or Kinda Blue {{Colorbox|#9eb0bf}} (Pixel 2); Just Black {{Colorbox|Black}} or Black and White {{Colorbox|Black}}{{Colorbox|White}} (Pixel 2 XL)
* Operating system: [[Android Oreo|Android 8.0 Oreo]]; upgradable to [[Android 11]]<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=Compare Pixel Phones and Specs |url=https://store.google.com/us/magazine/compare_pixel?hl=en-US|access-date=April 3, 2024 |website=Google Store |language=en-US}}</ref>

=== Pixel 3 and 3 XL ===
{{main|Pixel 3}}
[[File:Pixel 3 and 3 XL front.svg|thumb|Pixel 3 and Pixel 3 XL smartphones]]
[[File:Pixel 3 と Pixel 3 XL を初触。本体をギュッと握ると Google Assistant が立ち上がるのがおもしろい。 ワシントンDC (44519013945).jpg|thumb|upright|Pixel 3 and Pixel 3 XL on retail display with [[Pixel Buds]] and wireless charging accessories]]

Google announced the '''Pixel 3''' and '''Pixel 3 XL''' at an event on October 9, 2018, alongside several other products.

* Display: Pixel 3 5.5" OLED, 60&nbsp;Hz, 2160×1080 (18:9) pixel resolution; Pixel 3 XL 6.3" OLED, 60&nbsp;Hz, 2960×1440 (18.5:9) pixel resolution; both displays have Corning Gorilla Glass 5.
* Processor: Qualcomm [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems on chips#Snapdragon 800 series (2013–2021)|Snapdragon 845]]
* Storage: UFS 2.1 with 64&nbsp;GB or 128&nbsp;GB
* RAM: 4&nbsp;GB [[LPDDR#LPDDR4X|LPDDR4X]]
* Cameras: 12.2{{nbsp}}[[Pixel#Megapixel|MP]] rear camera Sony Exmor IMX363 with f/1.8 lens, IR laser-assisted autofocus, optical and electronic image stabilization; 8 MP front camera with f/1.8 lens and 75° lens, second front camera with 8 MP, f/2.2, fixed focus and 97° lens; [[stereophonic sound|stereo audio]] added to video recording<ref>{{cite web |title=Google Pixel 3 review |url=https://www.gsmarena.com/google_pixel_3-review-1847p5.php |website=GSMArena.com |page=5 |date=October 31, 2018 |quote=Audio is recorded in stereo at 192&nbsp;kbps - a new development after the Pixel 2's mono audio}}</ref>
* Battery: 2,915 mAh{{nbsp}}(Pixel 3); 3,430{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel 3 XL); both are non-removable and have fast charging and wireless charging
* Materials: Aluminum frame, matte glass back, IP68 water and dust resistance
* Colors: Just Black {{Colorbox|Black}}, Clearly White {{Colorbox|White}}, and Not Pink {{Colorbox|#decfca}}
* Operating system: [[Android Pie|Android 9.0 Pie]]; upgradable to [[Android 12]]<ref name=":3" />

=== Pixel 3a and 3a XL ===
[[File:GooglePixel3aAndroid12.jpg|thumb|Google Pixel 3a running Android 12]]
{{Main|Pixel 3a}}

On May 7, at [[Google I/O#2019|I/O 2019]], Google announced the '''Pixel 3a''' and '''Pixel 3a XL''', budget alternatives to the original two Pixel 3 devices.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/05/07/google-pixel-3a-xl/ |title=Google unveils the lower-cost Pixel 3a and Pixel 3a XL |work=[[Engadget]] |last=Fingas |first=Jon |date=May 7, 2019}}</ref>

* Display: Pixel 3a 5.6" OLED, 60&nbsp;Hz, 2220×1080 (18.5:9) pixel resolution; Pixel 3a XL 6" OLED, 60&nbsp;Hz, 2160×1080 (18:9) pixel resolution; both displays have Asahi [[Dragontrail]] Glass
* Processor: Qualcomm [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems on chips#Snapdragon 600 series (2013–2023)|Snapdragon 670]]
* Storage: 64&nbsp;GB
* RAM: 4&nbsp;GB [[LPDDR#LPDDR4X|LPDDR4X]]
* Cameras: 12.2{{nbsp}}[[Pixel#Megapixel|MP]] rear camera with f/1.8 lens, IR laser-assisted autofocus, optical and electronic image stabilization; 8 MP front camera with f/2.0 lens and 84° lens
* Headphone Jack
* Battery: 3,000{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel 3a); 3700{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel 3a XL); both are non-removable and have fast charging, but no wireless charging
* Materials: Polycarbonate body
* Colors: Just Black {{Colorbox|Black}}, Clearly White {{Colorbox|White}} and Purple-ish {{Colorbox|#d8dbef}}
* [[File:Google Pixel 5 back.jpg|thumb|Google Pixel 5 back in Just Black]]Operating system: [[Android 9]], upgradable to [[Android 12]]<ref name=":3" />

=== Pixel 4 and 4 XL ===
[[File:Google Pixel 5 front.jpg|thumb|Google Pixel 5 running Android 14]]
{{main|Pixel 4}}

Google announced the '''Pixel 4''' and '''Pixel 4 XL''' at an event on October 15, 2019, alongside several other products.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/9/16/20868670/google-pixel-4-event-date-time-october-15-announcement |title=Google announces October 15th hardware event for Pixel 4 |last=Welch |first=Chris |date=September 16, 2019 |website=The Verge |language=en|access-date=September 24, 2019}}</ref>

* Display: Pixel 4 5.7" OLED, 90&nbsp;Hz, 2280×1080 (19:9) pixel resolution; Pixel 4 XL 6.3" OLED, 90&nbsp;Hz, 3040×1440 (19:9) pixel resolution; both displays have Corning Gorilla Glass 5.
* Processor: Qualcomm [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems on chips#Snapdragon 800 series (2013–2021)|Snapdragon 855]]
* Storage: 64&nbsp;GB or 128&nbsp;GB
* RAM: 6&nbsp;GB [[LPDDR#LPDDR4X|LPDDR4X]]
* Cameras: 12.2{{nbsp}}[[Pixel#Megapixel|MP]] sensor with f/1.8 lens and 16{{nbsp}}MP telephoto sensor with f/2.4 lens, IR laser-assisted autofocus, optical and electronic image stabilization; 8{{nbsp}}MP front camera with f/2.0 lens and 90° lens
* Battery: 2,800{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel 4); 3,700{{nbsp}}mAh (Pixel 4 XL); both are non-removable and have fast charging and wireless charging
* Materials: Aluminum frame, matte or glossy glass back, IP68 water and dust resistance
* Colors: Just Black {{Colorbox|Black}}, Clearly White {{Colorbox|White}} and Oh So Orange {{Colorbox|#ff6a3f}}
* Operating system: [[Android 10]], upgradable to [[Android 13]]<ref name=":3" />

In 2019, Google offered a [[bug bounty program]] of up to $1.5{{nbsp}}million for the [[list of Google products#Processors|Titan M]] security chip built into Pixel 3, Pixel 3a and Pixel 4.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-50515647 |title=$1.5m 'reward' for spotting bugs in Google phones |date=November 22, 2019|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref>

=== Pixel 4a and 4a (5G) ===
{{Main|Pixel 4a}}
Google announced the '''Pixel 4a''' on August 3, 2020, and the '''Pixel 4a (5G)''' on September 30, 2020, as budget alternatives to the original two Pixel 4 devices.

* Display: 5.8" OLED (4a) 6.2" OLED (4a 5G), 60&nbsp;Hz, 2340×1080 (19.5:9) pixel resolution; the display uses Corning Gorilla Glass 3. Both have a hole punch for the front camera.
* Processor: Qualcomm [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems on chips#Snapdragon 700 series (2018–2022)|Snapdragon 730G]] (4a); Qualcomm [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems on chips#Snapdragon 700 series (2018–2022)|Snapdragon 765G]] (4a 5G)
* Storage: 128&nbsp;GB
* RAM: 6&nbsp;GB [[LPDDR#LPDDR4X|LPDDR4X]]
* Camera: 12.2{{nbsp}}[[Pixel#Megapixel|MP]] dual-pixel sensor with f/1.7{{nbsp}}lens, autofocus with dual-pixel phase detection, optical and electrical image stabilization. In addition, the 4a 5G has a 16&nbsp;MP ultrawide sensor with f/2.2&nbsp;lens. Both have an 8&nbsp;MP front camera with f/2.0&nbsp;lens.
* Battery: 3,140&nbsp;mAh (4a); Typical - 3,885&nbsp;mAh, Minimum - 3,800&nbsp;mAh (4a 5G); both are non-removable and feature all day battery as well as fast charging
* 3.5&nbsp;mm headset jack
* Materials: Polycarbonate body
* Colors: Just Black {{Colorbox|Black}} or Barely Blue {{Colorbox|#d0e7f7}} (Limited Edition) (Pixel 4a); Just Black {{Colorbox|Black}} or Clearly White {{Colorbox|White}} (Pixel 4a 5G)
* Operating System: [[Android 10]], upgradable to [[Android 13]] (4a); Android 11 (4a 5G), upgradable to [[Android 14]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Compare Pixel 4a 5G Tech Specs - Google Store |url=https://store.google.com/product/pixel_4a_5g_specs|access-date=September 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Pixel 4a Hardware Specs - Google Store |url=https://store.google.com/product/pixel_4a_specs|access-date=September 30, 2020}}</ref>

